1601/// Update the branch metadata for cloned call instructions.
1602static void updateCallProfile(Function *Callee, const ValueToValueMapTy &VMap,
1603 const ProfileCount &CalleeEntryCount,
1604 const CallBase &TheCall, ProfileSummaryInfo *PSI,
1605 BlockFrequencyInfo *CallerBFI) {
1606 if (!CalleeEntryCount.hasValue() || CalleeEntryCount.isSynthetic() ||
1607 CalleeEntryCount.getCount() < 1)
1608 return;
1609 auto CallSiteCount = PSI ? PSI->getProfileCount(TheCall, CallerBFI) : None;
1610 int64_t CallCount =
1611 std::min(CallSiteCount.getValueOr(0), CalleeEntryCount.getCount());
1612 updateProfileCallee(Callee, -CallCount, &VMap);
1613}
1614
1615void llvm::updateProfileCallee(
1616 Function *Callee, int64_t entryDelta,
1617 const ValueMap<const Value *, WeakTrackingVH> *VMap) {
1618 auto CalleeCount = Callee->getEntryCount();
1619 if (!CalleeCount.hasValue())
1620 return;
1621
1622 uint64_t priorEntryCount = CalleeCount.getCount();
1623 uint64_t newEntryCount;
1624
1625 // Since CallSiteCount is an estimate, it could exceed the original callee
1626 // count and has to be set to 0 so guard against underflow.
1627 if (entryDelta < 0 && static_cast<uint64_t>(-entryDelta) > priorEntryCount)
1628 newEntryCount = 0;
1629 else
1630 newEntryCount = priorEntryCount + entryDelta;
1631
1632 // During inlining ?
1633 if (VMap) {
1634 uint64_t cloneEntryCount = priorEntryCount - newEntryCount;
1635 for (auto Entry : *VMap)
1636 if (isa<CallInst>(Entry.first))
1637 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast_or_null<CallInst>(Entry.second))
1638 CI->updateProfWeight(cloneEntryCount, priorEntryCount);
1639 }
1640
1641 if (entryDelta) {
1642 Callee->setEntryCount(newEntryCount);
1643
1644 for (BasicBlock &BB : *Callee)
1645 // No need to update the callsite if it is pruned during inlining.
1646 if (!VMap || VMap->count(&BB))
1647 for (Instruction &I : BB)
1648 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I))
1649 CI->updateProfWeight(newEntryCount, priorEntryCount);
1650 }
1651}
1652
1653/// This function inlines the called function into the basic block of the
1654/// caller. This returns false if it is not possible to inline this call.
1655/// The program is still in a well defined state if this occurs though.
1656///
1657/// Note that this only does one level of inlining. For example, if the
1658/// instruction 'call B' is inlined, and 'B' calls 'C', then the call to 'C' now
1659/// exists in the instruction stream. Similarly this will inline a recursive
1660/// function by one level.
1661llvm::InlineResult llvm::InlineFunction(CallBase &CB, InlineFunctionInfo &IFI,
1662 AAResults *CalleeAAR,
1663 bool InsertLifetime,
1664 Function *ForwardVarArgsTo) {
1665 assert(CB.getParent() && CB.getFunction() && "Instruction not in function!");
1666
1667 // FIXME: we don't inline callbr yet.
1668 if (isa<CallBrInst>(CB))
1669 return InlineResult::failure("We don't inline callbr yet.");
1670
1671 // If IFI has any state in it, zap it before we fill it in.
1672 IFI.reset();
1673
1674 Function *CalledFunc = CB.getCalledFunction();
1675 if (!CalledFunc || // Can't inline external function or indirect
1676 CalledFunc->isDeclaration()) // call!
1677 return InlineResult::failure("external or indirect");
1678
1679 // The inliner does not know how to inline through calls with operand bundles
1680 // in general ...
1681 if (CB.hasOperandBundles()) {
1682 for (int i = 0, e = CB.getNumOperandBundles(); i != e; ++i) {
1683 uint32_t Tag = CB.getOperandBundleAt(i).getTagID();
1684 // ... but it knows how to inline through "deopt" operand bundles ...
1685 if (Tag == LLVMContext::OB_deopt)
1686 continue;
1687 // ... and "funclet" operand bundles.
1688 if (Tag == LLVMContext::OB_funclet)
1689 continue;
1690
1691 return InlineResult::failure("unsupported operand bundle");
1692 }
1693 }
1694
1695 // If the call to the callee cannot throw, set the 'nounwind' flag on any
1696 // calls that we inline.
1697 bool MarkNoUnwind = CB.doesNotThrow();
1698
1699 BasicBlock *OrigBB = CB.getParent();
1700 Function *Caller = OrigBB->getParent();
1701
1702 // GC poses two hazards to inlining, which only occur when the callee has GC:
1703 // 1. If the caller has no GC, then the callee's GC must be propagated to the
1704 // caller.
1705 // 2. If the caller has a differing GC, it is invalid to inline.
1706 if (CalledFunc->hasGC()) {
1707 if (!Caller->hasGC())
1708 Caller->setGC(CalledFunc->getGC());
1709 else if (CalledFunc->getGC() != Caller->getGC())
1710 return InlineResult::failure("incompatible GC");
1711 }
1712
1713 // Get the personality function from the callee if it contains a landing pad.
1714 Constant *CalledPersonality =
1715 CalledFunc->hasPersonalityFn()
1716 ? CalledFunc->getPersonalityFn()->stripPointerCasts()
1717 : nullptr;
1718
1719 // Find the personality function used by the landing pads of the caller. If it
1720 // exists, then check to see that it matches the personality function used in
1721 // the callee.
1722 Constant *CallerPersonality =
1723 Caller->hasPersonalityFn()
1724 ? Caller->getPersonalityFn()->stripPointerCasts()
1725 : nullptr;
1726 if (CalledPersonality) {
1727 if (!CallerPersonality)
1728 Caller->setPersonalityFn(CalledPersonality);
1729 // If the personality functions match, then we can perform the
1730 // inlining. Otherwise, we can't inline.
1731 // TODO: This isn't 100% true. Some personality functions are proper
1732 // supersets of others and can be used in place of the other.
1733 else if (CalledPersonality != CallerPersonality)
1734 return InlineResult::failure("incompatible personality");
1735 }
1736
1737 // We need to figure out which funclet the callsite was in so that we may
1738 // properly nest the callee.
1739 Instruction *CallSiteEHPad = nullptr;
1740 if (CallerPersonality) {
1741 EHPersonality Personality = classifyEHPersonality(CallerPersonality);
1742 if (isScopedEHPersonality(Personality)) {
1743 Optional<OperandBundleUse> ParentFunclet =
1744 CB.getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_funclet);
1745 if (ParentFunclet)
1746 CallSiteEHPad = cast<FuncletPadInst>(ParentFunclet->Inputs.front());
1747
1748 // OK, the inlining site is legal. What about the target function?
1749
1750 if (CallSiteEHPad) {
1751 if (Personality == EHPersonality::MSVC_CXX) {
1752 // The MSVC personality cannot tolerate catches getting inlined into
1753 // cleanup funclets.
1754 if (isa<CleanupPadInst>(CallSiteEHPad)) {
1755 // Ok, the call site is within a cleanuppad. Let's check the callee
1756 // for catchpads.
1757 for (const BasicBlock &CalledBB : *CalledFunc) {
1758 if (isa<CatchSwitchInst>(CalledBB.getFirstNonPHI()))
1759 return InlineResult::failure("catch in cleanup funclet");
1760 }
1761 }
1762 } else if (isAsynchronousEHPersonality(Personality)) {
1763 // SEH is even less tolerant, there may not be any sort of exceptional
1764 // funclet in the callee.
1765 for (const BasicBlock &CalledBB : *CalledFunc) {
1766 if (CalledBB.isEHPad())
1767 return InlineResult::failure("SEH in cleanup funclet");
1768 }
1769 }
1770 }
1771 }
1772 }
1773
1774 // Determine if we are dealing with a call in an EHPad which does not unwind
1775 // to caller.
1776 bool EHPadForCallUnwindsLocally = false;
1777 if (CallSiteEHPad && isa<CallInst>(CB)) {
1778 UnwindDestMemoTy FuncletUnwindMap;
1779 Value *CallSiteUnwindDestToken =
1780 getUnwindDestToken(CallSiteEHPad, FuncletUnwindMap);
1781
1782 EHPadForCallUnwindsLocally =
1783 CallSiteUnwindDestToken &&
1784 !isa<ConstantTokenNone>(CallSiteUnwindDestToken);
1785 }
1786
1787 // Get an iterator to the last basic block in the function, which will have
1788 // the new function inlined after it.
1789 Function::iterator LastBlock = --Caller->end();
1790
1791 // Make sure to capture all of the return instructions from the cloned
1792 // function.
1793 SmallVector<ReturnInst*, 8> Returns;
1794 ClonedCodeInfo InlinedFunctionInfo;
1795 Function::iterator FirstNewBlock;
1796
1797 { // Scope to destroy VMap after cloning.
1798 ValueToValueMapTy VMap;
1799 // Keep a list of pair (dst, src) to emit byval initializations.
1800 SmallVector<std::pair<Value*, Value*>, 4> ByValInit;
1801
1802 // When inlining a function that contains noalias scope metadata,
1803 // this metadata needs to be cloned so that the inlined blocks
1804 // have different "unique scopes" at every call site.
1805 // Track the metadata that must be cloned. Do this before other changes to
1806 // the function, so that we do not get in trouble when inlining caller ==
1807 // callee.
1808 ScopedAliasMetadataDeepCloner SAMetadataCloner(CB.getCalledFunction());
1809
1810 auto &DL = Caller->getParent()->getDataLayout();
1811
1812 // Calculate the vector of arguments to pass into the function cloner, which
1813 // matches up the formal to the actual argument values.
1814 auto AI = CB.arg_begin();
1815 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
1816 for (Function::arg_iterator I = CalledFunc->arg_begin(),
1817 E = CalledFunc->arg_end(); I != E; ++I, ++AI, ++ArgNo) {
1818 Value *ActualArg = *AI;
1819
1820 // When byval arguments actually inlined, we need to make the copy implied
1821 // by them explicit. However, we don't do this if the callee is readonly
1822 // or readnone, because the copy would be unneeded: the callee doesn't
1823 // modify the struct.
1824 if (CB.isByValArgument(ArgNo)) {
1825 ActualArg = HandleByValArgument(ActualArg, &CB, CalledFunc, IFI,
1826 CalledFunc->getParamAlignment(ArgNo));
1827 if (ActualArg != *AI)
1828 ByValInit.push_back(std::make_pair(ActualArg, (Value*) *AI));
1829 }
1830
1831 VMap[&*I] = ActualArg;
1832 }
1833
1834 // TODO: Remove this when users have been updated to the assume bundles.
1835 // Add alignment assumptions if necessary. We do this before the inlined
1836 // instructions are actually cloned into the caller so that we can easily
1837 // check what will be known at the start of the inlined code.
1838 AddAlignmentAssumptions(CB, IFI);
1839
1840 AssumptionCache *AC =
1841 IFI.GetAssumptionCache ? &IFI.GetAssumptionCache(*Caller) : nullptr;
1842
1843 /// Preserve all attributes on of the call and its parameters.
1844 salvageKnowledge(&CB, AC);
1845
1846 // We want the inliner to prune the code as it copies. We would LOVE to
1847 // have no dead or constant instructions leftover after inlining occurs
1848 // (which can happen, e.g., because an argument was constant), but we'll be
1849 // happy with whatever the cloner can do.
1850 CloneAndPruneFunctionInto(Caller, CalledFunc, VMap,
1851 /*ModuleLevelChanges=*/false, Returns, ".i",
1852 &InlinedFunctionInfo, &CB);
1853 // Remember the first block that is newly cloned over.
1854 FirstNewBlock = LastBlock; ++FirstNewBlock;
1855
1856 if (IFI.CallerBFI != nullptr && IFI.CalleeBFI != nullptr)
1857 // Update the BFI of blocks cloned into the caller.
1858 updateCallerBFI(OrigBB, VMap, IFI.CallerBFI, IFI.CalleeBFI,
1859 CalledFunc->front());
1860
1861 updateCallProfile(CalledFunc, VMap, CalledFunc->getEntryCount(), CB,
1862 IFI.PSI, IFI.CallerBFI);
1863
1864 // Inject byval arguments initialization.
1865 for (std::pair<Value*, Value*> &Init : ByValInit)
1866 HandleByValArgumentInit(Init.first, Init.second, Caller->getParent(),
1867 &*FirstNewBlock, IFI);
1868
1869 Optional<OperandBundleUse> ParentDeopt =
1870 CB.getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_deopt);
1871 if (ParentDeopt) {
1872 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 2> OpDefs;
1873
1874 for (auto &VH : InlinedFunctionInfo.OperandBundleCallSites) {
1875 CallBase *ICS = dyn_cast_or_null<CallBase>(VH);
1876 if (!ICS)
1877 continue; // instruction was DCE'd or RAUW'ed to undef
1878
1879 OpDefs.clear();
1880
1881 OpDefs.reserve(ICS->getNumOperandBundles());
1882
1883 for (unsigned COBi = 0, COBe = ICS->getNumOperandBundles(); COBi < COBe;
1884 ++COBi) {
1885 auto ChildOB = ICS->getOperandBundleAt(COBi);
1886 if (ChildOB.getTagID() != LLVMContext::OB_deopt) {
1887 // If the inlined call has other operand bundles, let them be
1888 OpDefs.emplace_back(ChildOB);
1889 continue;
1890 }
1891
1892 // It may be useful to separate this logic (of handling operand
1893 // bundles) out to a separate "policy" component if this gets crowded.
1894 // Prepend the parent's deoptimization continuation to the newly
1895 // inlined call's deoptimization continuation.
1896 std::vector<Value *> MergedDeoptArgs;
1897 MergedDeoptArgs.reserve(ParentDeopt->Inputs.size() +
1898 ChildOB.Inputs.size());
1899
1900 llvm::append_range(MergedDeoptArgs, ParentDeopt->Inputs);
1901 llvm::append_range(MergedDeoptArgs, ChildOB.Inputs);
1902
1903 OpDefs.emplace_back("deopt", std::move(MergedDeoptArgs));
1904 }
1905
1906 Instruction *NewI = CallBase::Create(ICS, OpDefs, ICS);
1907
1908 // Note: the RAUW does the appropriate fixup in VMap, so we need to do
1909 // this even if the call returns void.
1910 ICS->replaceAllUsesWith(NewI);
1911
1912 VH = nullptr;
1913 ICS->eraseFromParent();
1914 }
1915 }
1916
1917 // Update the callgraph if requested.
1918 if (IFI.CG)
1919 UpdateCallGraphAfterInlining(CB, FirstNewBlock, VMap, IFI);
1920
1921 // For 'nodebug' functions, the associated DISubprogram is always null.
1922 // Conservatively avoid propagating the callsite debug location to
1923 // instructions inlined from a function whose DISubprogram is not null.
1924 fixupLineNumbers(Caller, FirstNewBlock, &CB,
1925 CalledFunc->getSubprogram() != nullptr);
1926
1927 // Now clone the inlined noalias scope metadata.
1928 SAMetadataCloner.clone();
1929 SAMetadataCloner.remap(VMap);
1930
1931 // Add noalias metadata if necessary.
1932 AddAliasScopeMetadata(CB, VMap, DL, CalleeAAR);
1933
1934 // Clone return attributes on the callsite into the calls within the inlined
1935 // function which feed into its return value.
1936 AddReturnAttributes(CB, VMap);
1937
1938 // Propagate metadata on the callsite if necessary.
1939 PropagateCallSiteMetadata(CB, VMap);
1940
1941 // Register any cloned assumptions.
1942 if (IFI.GetAssumptionCache)
1943 for (BasicBlock &NewBlock :
1944 make_range(FirstNewBlock->getIterator(), Caller->end()))
1945 for (Instruction &I : NewBlock)
1946 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(&I))
1947 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::assume)
1948 IFI.GetAssumptionCache(*Caller).registerAssumption(II);
1949 }
1950
1951 // If there are any alloca instructions in the block that used to be the entry
1952 // block for the callee, move them to the entry block of the caller. First
1953 // calculate which instruction they should be inserted before. We insert the
1954 // instructions at the end of the current alloca list.
1955 {
1956 BasicBlock::iterator InsertPoint = Caller->begin()->begin();
1957 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = FirstNewBlock->begin(),
1958 E = FirstNewBlock->end(); I != E; ) {
1959 AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(I++);
1960 if (!AI) continue;
1961
1962 // If the alloca is now dead, remove it. This often occurs due to code
1963 // specialization.
1964 if (AI->use_empty()) {
1965 AI->eraseFromParent();
1966 continue;
1967 }
1968
1969 if (!allocaWouldBeStaticInEntry(AI))
1970 continue;
1971
1972 // Keep track of the static allocas that we inline into the caller.
1973 IFI.StaticAllocas.push_back(AI);
1974
1975 // Scan for the block of allocas that we can move over, and move them
1976 // all at once.
1977 while (isa<AllocaInst>(I) &&
1978 !cast<AllocaInst>(I)->use_empty() &&
1979 allocaWouldBeStaticInEntry(cast<AllocaInst>(I))) {
1980 IFI.StaticAllocas.push_back(cast<AllocaInst>(I));
1981 ++I;
1982 }
1983
1984 // Transfer all of the allocas over in a block. Using splice means
1985 // that the instructions aren't removed from the symbol table, then
1986 // reinserted.
1987 Caller->getEntryBlock().getInstList().splice(
1988 InsertPoint, FirstNewBlock->getInstList(), AI->getIterator(), I);
1989 }
1990 }
1991
1992 SmallVector<Value*,4> VarArgsToForward;
1993 SmallVector<AttributeSet, 4> VarArgsAttrs;
1994 for (unsigned i = CalledFunc->getFunctionType()->getNumParams();
1995 i < CB.getNumArgOperands(); i++) {
1996 VarArgsToForward.push_back(CB.getArgOperand(i));
1997 VarArgsAttrs.push_back(CB.getAttributes().getParamAttributes(i));
1998 }
1999
2000 bool InlinedMustTailCalls = false, InlinedDeoptimizeCalls = false;
2001 if (InlinedFunctionInfo.ContainsCalls) {
2002 CallInst::TailCallKind CallSiteTailKind = CallInst::TCK_None;
2003 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&CB))
2004 CallSiteTailKind = CI->getTailCallKind();
2005
2006 // For inlining purposes, the "notail" marker is the same as no marker.
2007 if (CallSiteTailKind == CallInst::TCK_NoTail)
2008 CallSiteTailKind = CallInst::TCK_None;
2009
2010 for (Function::iterator BB = FirstNewBlock, E = Caller->end(); BB != E;
2011 ++BB) {
2012 for (auto II = BB->begin(); II != BB->end();) {
2013 Instruction &I = *II++;
2014 CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I);
2015 if (!CI)
2016 continue;
2017
2018 // Forward varargs from inlined call site to calls to the
2019 // ForwardVarArgsTo function, if requested, and to musttail calls.
2020 if (!VarArgsToForward.empty() &&
2021 ((ForwardVarArgsTo &&
2022 CI->getCalledFunction() == ForwardVarArgsTo) ||
2023 CI->isMustTailCall())) {
2024 // Collect attributes for non-vararg parameters.
2025 AttributeList Attrs = CI->getAttributes();
2026 SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> ArgAttrs;
2027 if (!Attrs.isEmpty() || !VarArgsAttrs.empty()) {
2028 for (unsigned ArgNo = 0;
2029 ArgNo < CI->getFunctionType()->getNumParams(); ++ArgNo)
2030 ArgAttrs.push_back(Attrs.getParamAttributes(ArgNo));
2031 }
2032
2033 // Add VarArg attributes.
2034 ArgAttrs.append(VarArgsAttrs.begin(), VarArgsAttrs.end());
2035 Attrs = AttributeList::get(CI->getContext(), Attrs.getFnAttributes(),
2036 Attrs.getRetAttributes(), ArgAttrs);
2037 // Add VarArgs to existing parameters.
2038 SmallVector<Value *, 6> Params(CI->arg_operands());
2039 Params.append(VarArgsToForward.begin(), VarArgsToForward.end());
2040 CallInst *NewCI = CallInst::Create(
2041 CI->getFunctionType(), CI->getCalledOperand(), Params, "", CI);
2042 NewCI->setDebugLoc(CI->getDebugLoc());
2043 NewCI->setAttributes(Attrs);
2044 NewCI->setCallingConv(CI->getCallingConv());
2045 CI->replaceAllUsesWith(NewCI);
2046 CI->eraseFromParent();
2047 CI = NewCI;
2048 }
2049
2050 if (Function *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
2051 InlinedDeoptimizeCalls |=
2052 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_deoptimize;
2053
2054 // We need to reduce the strength of any inlined tail calls. For
2055 // musttail, we have to avoid introducing potential unbounded stack
2056 // growth. For example, if functions 'f' and 'g' are mutually recursive
2057 // with musttail, we can inline 'g' into 'f' so long as we preserve
2058 // musttail on the cloned call to 'f'. If either the inlined call site
2059 // or the cloned call site is *not* musttail, the program already has
2060 // one frame of stack growth, so it's safe to remove musttail. Here is
2061 // a table of example transformations:
2062 //
2063 // f -> musttail g -> musttail f ==> f -> musttail f
2064 // f -> musttail g -> tail f ==> f -> tail f
2065 // f -> g -> musttail f ==> f -> f
2066 // f -> g -> tail f ==> f -> f
2067 //
2068 // Inlined notail calls should remain notail calls.
2069 CallInst::TailCallKind ChildTCK = CI->getTailCallKind();
2070 if (ChildTCK != CallInst::TCK_NoTail)
2071 ChildTCK = std::min(CallSiteTailKind, ChildTCK);
2072 CI->setTailCallKind(ChildTCK);
2073 InlinedMustTailCalls |= CI->isMustTailCall();
2074
2075 // Calls inlined through a 'nounwind' call site should be marked
2076 // 'nounwind'.
2077 if (MarkNoUnwind)
2078 CI->setDoesNotThrow();
2079 }
2080 }
2081 }
2082
2083 // Leave lifetime markers for the static alloca's, scoping them to the
2084 // function we just inlined.
2085 if (InsertLifetime && !IFI.StaticAllocas.empty()) {
2086 IRBuilder<> builder(&FirstNewBlock->front());
2087 for (unsigned ai = 0, ae = IFI.StaticAllocas.size(); ai != ae; ++ai) {
2088 AllocaInst *AI = IFI.StaticAllocas[ai];
2089 // Don't mark swifterror allocas. They can't have bitcast uses.
2090 if (AI->isSwiftError())
2091 continue;
2092
2093 // If the alloca is already scoped to something smaller than the whole
2094 // function then there's no need to add redundant, less accurate markers.
2095 if (hasLifetimeMarkers(AI))
2096 continue;
2097
2098 // Try to determine the size of the allocation.
2099 ConstantInt *AllocaSize = nullptr;
2100 if (ConstantInt *AIArraySize =
2101 dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(AI->getArraySize())) {
2102 auto &DL = Caller->getParent()->getDataLayout();
2103 Type *AllocaType = AI->getAllocatedType();
2104 TypeSize AllocaTypeSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(AllocaType);
2105 uint64_t AllocaArraySize = AIArraySize->getLimitedValue();
2106
2107 // Don't add markers for zero-sized allocas.
2108 if (AllocaArraySize == 0)
2109 continue;
2110
2111 // Check that array size doesn't saturate uint64_t and doesn't
2112 // overflow when it's multiplied by type size.
2113 if (!AllocaTypeSize.isScalable() &&
2114 AllocaArraySize != std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max() &&
2115 std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max() / AllocaArraySize >=
2116 AllocaTypeSize.getFixedSize()) {
2117 AllocaSize = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt64Ty(AI->getContext()),
2118 AllocaArraySize * AllocaTypeSize);
2119 }
2120 }
2121
2122 builder.CreateLifetimeStart(AI, AllocaSize);
2123 for (ReturnInst *RI : Returns) {
2124 // Don't insert llvm.lifetime.end calls between a musttail or deoptimize
2125 // call and a return. The return kills all local allocas.
2126 if (InlinedMustTailCalls &&
2127 RI->getParent()->getTerminatingMustTailCall())
2128 continue;
2129 if (InlinedDeoptimizeCalls &&
2130 RI->getParent()->getTerminatingDeoptimizeCall())
2131 continue;
2132 IRBuilder<>(RI).CreateLifetimeEnd(AI, AllocaSize);
2133 }
2134 }
2135 }
2136
2137 // If the inlined code contained dynamic alloca instructions, wrap the inlined
2138 // code with llvm.stacksave/llvm.stackrestore intrinsics.
2139 if (InlinedFunctionInfo.ContainsDynamicAllocas) {
2140 Module *M = Caller->getParent();
2141 // Get the two intrinsics we care about.
2142 Function *StackSave = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::stacksave);
2143 Function *StackRestore=Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M,Intrinsic::stackrestore);
2144
2145 // Insert the llvm.stacksave.
2146 CallInst *SavedPtr = IRBuilder<>(&*FirstNewBlock, FirstNewBlock->begin())
2147 .CreateCall(StackSave, {}, "savedstack");
2148
2149 // Insert a call to llvm.stackrestore before any return instructions in the
2150 // inlined function.
2151 for (ReturnInst *RI : Returns) {
2152 // Don't insert llvm.stackrestore calls between a musttail or deoptimize
2153 // call and a return. The return will restore the stack pointer.
2154 if (InlinedMustTailCalls && RI->getParent()->getTerminatingMustTailCall())
2155 continue;
2156 if (InlinedDeoptimizeCalls && RI->getParent()->getTerminatingDeoptimizeCall())
2157 continue;
2158 IRBuilder<>(RI).CreateCall(StackRestore, SavedPtr);
2159 }
2160 }
2161
2162 // If we are inlining for an invoke instruction, we must make sure to rewrite
2163 // any call instructions into invoke instructions. This is sensitive to which
2164 // funclet pads were top-level in the inlinee, so must be done before
2165 // rewriting the "parent pad" links.
2166 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&CB)) {
2167 BasicBlock *UnwindDest = II->getUnwindDest();
2168 Instruction *FirstNonPHI = UnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI();
2169 if (isa<LandingPadInst>(FirstNonPHI)) {
2170 HandleInlinedLandingPad(II, &*FirstNewBlock, InlinedFunctionInfo);
2171 } else {
2172 HandleInlinedEHPad(II, &*FirstNewBlock, InlinedFunctionInfo);
2173 }
2174 }
2175
2176 // Update the lexical scopes of the new funclets and callsites.
2177 // Anything that had 'none' as its parent is now nested inside the callsite's
2178 // EHPad.
2179
2180 if (CallSiteEHPad) {
2181 for (Function::iterator BB = FirstNewBlock->getIterator(),
2182 E = Caller->end();
2183 BB != E; ++BB) {
2184 // Add bundle operands to any top-level call sites.
2185 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
2186 for (BasicBlock::iterator BBI = BB->begin(), E = BB->end(); BBI != E;) {
2187 CallBase *I = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&*BBI++);
2188 if (!I)
2189 continue;
2190
2191 // Skip call sites which are nounwind intrinsics.
2192 auto *CalledFn =
2193 dyn_cast<Function>(I->getCalledOperand()->stripPointerCasts());
2194 if (CalledFn && CalledFn->isIntrinsic() && I->doesNotThrow())
2195 continue;
2196
2197 // Skip call sites which already have a "funclet" bundle.
2198 if (I->getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_funclet))
2199 continue;
2200
2201 I->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
2202 OpBundles.emplace_back("funclet", CallSiteEHPad);
2203
2204 Instruction *NewInst = CallBase::Create(I, OpBundles, I);
2205 NewInst->takeName(I);
2206 I->replaceAllUsesWith(NewInst);
2207 I->eraseFromParent();
2208
2209 OpBundles.clear();
2210 }
2211
2212 // It is problematic if the inlinee has a cleanupret which unwinds to
2213 // caller and we inline it into a call site which doesn't unwind but into
2214 // an EH pad that does. Such an edge must be dynamically unreachable.
2215 // As such, we replace the cleanupret with unreachable.
2216 if (auto *CleanupRet = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(BB->getTerminator()))
2217 if (CleanupRet->unwindsToCaller() && EHPadForCallUnwindsLocally)
2218 changeToUnreachable(CleanupRet, /*UseLLVMTrap=*/false);
2219
2220 Instruction *I = BB->getFirstNonPHI();
2221 if (!I->isEHPad())
2222 continue;
2223
2224 if (auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(I)) {
2225 if (isa<ConstantTokenNone>(CatchSwitch->getParentPad()))
2226 CatchSwitch->setParentPad(CallSiteEHPad);
2227 } else {
2228 auto *FPI = cast<FuncletPadInst>(I);
2229 if (isa<ConstantTokenNone>(FPI->getParentPad()))
2230 FPI->setParentPad(CallSiteEHPad);
2231 }
2232 }
2233 }
2234
2235 if (InlinedDeoptimizeCalls) {
2236 // We need to at least remove the deoptimizing returns from the Return set,
2237 // so that the control flow from those returns does not get merged into the
2238 // caller (but terminate it instead). If the caller's return type does not
2239 // match the callee's return type, we also need to change the return type of
2240 // the intrinsic.
2241 if (Caller->getReturnType() == CB.getType()) {
2242 llvm::erase_if(Returns, [](ReturnInst *RI) {
2243 return RI->getParent()->getTerminatingDeoptimizeCall() != nullptr;
2244 });
2245 } else {
2246 SmallVector<ReturnInst *, 8> NormalReturns;
2247 Function *NewDeoptIntrinsic = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
2248 Caller->getParent(), Intrinsic::experimental_deoptimize,
2249 {Caller->getReturnType()});
2250
2251 for (ReturnInst *RI : Returns) {
2252 CallInst *DeoptCall = RI->getParent()->getTerminatingDeoptimizeCall();
2253 if (!DeoptCall) {
2254 NormalReturns.push_back(RI);
2255 continue;
2256 }
2257
2258 // The calling convention on the deoptimize call itself may be bogus,
2259 // since the code we're inlining may have undefined behavior (and may
2260 // never actually execute at runtime); but all
2261 // @llvm.experimental.deoptimize declarations have to have the same
2262 // calling convention in a well-formed module.
2263 auto CallingConv = DeoptCall->getCalledFunction()->getCallingConv();
2264 NewDeoptIntrinsic->setCallingConv(CallingConv);
2265 auto *CurBB = RI->getParent();
2266 RI->eraseFromParent();
2267
2268 SmallVector<Value *, 4> CallArgs(DeoptCall->args());
2269
2270 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
2271 DeoptCall->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
2272 DeoptCall->eraseFromParent();
2273 assert(!OpBundles.empty() &&
2274 "Expected at least the deopt operand bundle");
2275
2276 IRBuilder<> Builder(CurBB);
2277 CallInst *NewDeoptCall =
2278 Builder.CreateCall(NewDeoptIntrinsic, CallArgs, OpBundles);
2279 NewDeoptCall->setCallingConv(CallingConv);
2280 if (NewDeoptCall->getType()->isVoidTy())
2281 Builder.CreateRetVoid();
2282 else
2283 Builder.CreateRet(NewDeoptCall);
2284 }
2285
2286 // Leave behind the normal returns so we can merge control flow.
2287 std::swap(Returns, NormalReturns);
2288 }
2289 }
2290
2291 // Handle any inlined musttail call sites. In order for a new call site to be
2292 // musttail, the source of the clone and the inlined call site must have been
2293 // musttail. Therefore it's safe to return without merging control into the
2294 // phi below.
2295 if (InlinedMustTailCalls) {
2296 // Check if we need to bitcast the result of any musttail calls.
2297 Type *NewRetTy = Caller->getReturnType();
2298 bool NeedBitCast = !CB.use_empty() && CB.getType() != NewRetTy;
2299
2300 // Handle the returns preceded by musttail calls separately.
2301 SmallVector<ReturnInst *, 8> NormalReturns;
2302 for (ReturnInst *RI : Returns) {
2303 CallInst *ReturnedMustTail =
2304 RI->getParent()->getTerminatingMustTailCall();
2305 if (!ReturnedMustTail) {
2306 NormalReturns.push_back(RI);
2307 continue;
2308 }
2309 if (!NeedBitCast)
2310 continue;
2311
2312 // Delete the old return and any preceding bitcast.
2313 BasicBlock *CurBB = RI->getParent();
2314 auto *OldCast = dyn_cast_or_null<BitCastInst>(RI->getReturnValue());
2315 RI->eraseFromParent();
2316 if (OldCast)
2317 OldCast->eraseFromParent();
2318
2319 // Insert a new bitcast and return with the right type.
2320 IRBuilder<> Builder(CurBB);
2321 Builder.CreateRet(Builder.CreateBitCast(ReturnedMustTail, NewRetTy));
2322 }
2323
2324 // Leave behind the normal returns so we can merge control flow.
2325 std::swap(Returns, NormalReturns);
2326 }
2327
2328 // Now that all of the transforms on the inlined code have taken place but
2329 // before we splice the inlined code into the CFG and lose track of which
2330 // blocks were actually inlined, collect the call sites. We only do this if
2331 // call graph updates weren't requested, as those provide value handle based
2332 // tracking of inlined call sites instead.
2333 if (InlinedFunctionInfo.ContainsCalls && !IFI.CG) {
2334 // Otherwise just collect the raw call sites that were inlined.
2335 for (BasicBlock &NewBB :
2336 make_range(FirstNewBlock->getIterator(), Caller->end()))
2337 for (Instruction &I : NewBB)
2338 if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I))
2339 IFI.InlinedCallSites.push_back(CB);
2340 }
2341
2342 // If we cloned in _exactly one_ basic block, and if that block ends in a
2343 // return instruction, we splice the body of the inlined callee directly into
2344 // the calling basic block.
2345 if (Returns.size() == 1 && std::distance(FirstNewBlock, Caller->end()) == 1) {
2346 // Move all of the instructions right before the call.
2347 OrigBB->getInstList().splice(CB.getIterator(), FirstNewBlock->getInstList(),
2348 FirstNewBlock->begin(), FirstNewBlock->end());
2349 // Remove the cloned basic block.
2350 Caller->getBasicBlockList().pop_back();
2351
2352 // If the call site was an invoke instruction, add a branch to the normal
2353 // destination.
2354 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&CB)) {
2355 BranchInst *NewBr = BranchInst::Create(II->getNormalDest(), &CB);
2356 NewBr->setDebugLoc(Returns[0]->getDebugLoc());
2357 }
2358
2359 // If the return instruction returned a value, replace uses of the call with
2360 // uses of the returned value.
2361 if (!CB.use_empty()) {
2362 ReturnInst *R = Returns[0];
2363 if (&CB == R->getReturnValue())
2364 CB.replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(CB.getType()));
2365 else
2366 CB.replaceAllUsesWith(R->getReturnValue());
2367 }
2368 // Since we are now done with the Call/Invoke, we can delete it.
2369 CB.eraseFromParent();
2370
2371 // Since we are now done with the return instruction, delete it also.
2372 Returns[0]->eraseFromParent();
2373
2374 // We are now done with the inlining.
2375 return InlineResult::success();
2376 }
2377
2378 // Otherwise, we have the normal case, of more than one block to inline or
2379 // multiple return sites.
2380
2381 // We want to clone the entire callee function into the hole between the
2382 // "starter" and "ender" blocks. How we accomplish this depends on whether
2383 // this is an invoke instruction or a call instruction.
2384 BasicBlock *AfterCallBB;
2385 BranchInst *CreatedBranchToNormalDest = nullptr;
2386 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&CB)) {
2387
2388 // Add an unconditional branch to make this look like the CallInst case...
2389 CreatedBranchToNormalDest = BranchInst::Create(II->getNormalDest(), &CB);
2390
2391 // Split the basic block. This guarantees that no PHI nodes will have to be
2392 // updated due to new incoming edges, and make the invoke case more
2393 // symmetric to the call case.
2394 AfterCallBB =
2395 OrigBB->splitBasicBlock(CreatedBranchToNormalDest->getIterator(),
2396 CalledFunc->getName() + ".exit");
2397
2398 } else { // It's a call
2399 // If this is a call instruction, we need to split the basic block that
2400 // the call lives in.
2401 //
2402 AfterCallBB = OrigBB->splitBasicBlock(CB.getIterator(),
2403 CalledFunc->getName() + ".exit");
2404 }
2405
2406 if (IFI.CallerBFI) {
2407 // Copy original BB's block frequency to AfterCallBB
2408 IFI.CallerBFI->setBlockFreq(
2409 AfterCallBB, IFI.CallerBFI->getBlockFreq(OrigBB).getFrequency());
2410 }
2411
2412 // Change the branch that used to go to AfterCallBB to branch to the first
2413 // basic block of the inlined function.
2414 //
2415 Instruction *Br = OrigBB->getTerminator();
2416 assert(Br && Br->getOpcode() == Instruction::Br &&
2417 "splitBasicBlock broken!");
2418 Br->setOperand(0, &*FirstNewBlock);
2419
2420 // Now that the function is correct, make it a little bit nicer. In
2421 // particular, move the basic blocks inserted from the end of the function
2422 // into the space made by splitting the source basic block.
2423 Caller->getBasicBlockList().splice(AfterCallBB->getIterator(),
2424 Caller->getBasicBlockList(), FirstNewBlock,
2425 Caller->end());
2426
2427 // Handle all of the return instructions that we just cloned in, and eliminate
2428 // any users of the original call/invoke instruction.
2429 Type *RTy = CalledFunc->getReturnType();
2430
2431 PHINode *PHI = nullptr;
2432 if (Returns.size() > 1) {
2433 // The PHI node should go at the front of the new basic block to merge all
2434 // possible incoming values.
2435 if (!CB.use_empty()) {
2436 PHI = PHINode::Create(RTy, Returns.size(), CB.getName(),
2437 &AfterCallBB->front());
2438 // Anything that used the result of the function call should now use the
2439 // PHI node as their operand.
2440 CB.replaceAllUsesWith(PHI);
2441 }
2442
2443 // Loop over all of the return instructions adding entries to the PHI node
2444 // as appropriate.
2445 if (PHI) {
2446 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Returns.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2447 ReturnInst *RI = Returns[i];
2448 assert(RI->getReturnValue()->getType() == PHI->getType() &&
2449 "Ret value not consistent in function!");
2450 PHI->addIncoming(RI->getReturnValue(), RI->getParent());
2451 }
2452 }
2453
2454 // Add a branch to the merge points and remove return instructions.
2455 DebugLoc Loc;
2456 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Returns.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2457 ReturnInst *RI = Returns[i];
2458 BranchInst* BI = BranchInst::Create(AfterCallBB, RI);
2459 Loc = RI->getDebugLoc();
2460 BI->setDebugLoc(Loc);
2461 RI->eraseFromParent();
2462 }
2463 // We need to set the debug location to *somewhere* inside the
2464 // inlined function. The line number may be nonsensical, but the
2465 // instruction will at least be associated with the right
2466 // function.
2467 if (CreatedBranchToNormalDest)
2468 CreatedBranchToNormalDest->setDebugLoc(Loc);
2469 } else if (!Returns.empty()) {
2470 // Otherwise, if there is exactly one return value, just replace anything
2471 // using the return value of the call with the computed value.
2472 if (!CB.use_empty()) {
2473 if (&CB == Returns[0]->getReturnValue())
2474 CB.replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(CB.getType()));
2475 else
2476 CB.replaceAllUsesWith(Returns[0]->getReturnValue());
2477 }
2478
2479 // Update PHI nodes that use the ReturnBB to use the AfterCallBB.
2480 BasicBlock *ReturnBB = Returns[0]->getParent();
2481 ReturnBB->replaceAllUsesWith(AfterCallBB);
2482
2483 // Splice the code from the return block into the block that it will return
2484 // to, which contains the code that was after the call.
2485 AfterCallBB->getInstList().splice(AfterCallBB->begin(),
2486 ReturnBB->getInstList());
2487
2488 if (CreatedBranchToNormalDest)
2489 CreatedBranchToNormalDest->setDebugLoc(Returns[0]->getDebugLoc());
2490
2491 // Delete the return instruction now and empty ReturnBB now.
2492 Returns[0]->eraseFromParent();
2493 ReturnBB->eraseFromParent();
2494 } else if (!CB.use_empty()) {
2495 // No returns, but something is using the return value of the call. Just
2496 // nuke the result.
2497 CB.replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(CB.getType()));
2498 }
2499
2500 // Since we are now done with the Call/Invoke, we can delete it.
2501 CB.eraseFromParent();
2502
2503 // If we inlined any musttail calls and the original return is now
2504 // unreachable, delete it. It can only contain a bitcast and ret.
2505 if (InlinedMustTailCalls && pred_empty(AfterCallBB))
2506 AfterCallBB->eraseFromParent();
2507
2508 // We should always be able to fold the entry block of the function into the
2509 // single predecessor of the block...
2510 assert(cast<BranchInst>(Br)->isUnconditional() && "splitBasicBlock broken!");
2511 BasicBlock *CalleeEntry = cast<BranchInst>(Br)->getSuccessor(0);
2512
2513 // Splice the code entry block into calling block, right before the
2514 // unconditional branch.
2515 CalleeEntry->replaceAllUsesWith(OrigBB); // Update PHI nodes
2516 OrigBB->getInstList().splice(Br->getIterator(), CalleeEntry->getInstList());
2517
2518 // Remove the unconditional branch.
2519 OrigBB->getInstList().erase(Br);
2520
2521 // Now we can remove the CalleeEntry block, which is now empty.
2522 Caller->getBasicBlockList().erase(CalleeEntry);
2523
2524 // If we inserted a phi node, check to see if it has a single value (e.g. all
2525 // the entries are the same or undef). If so, remove the PHI so it doesn't
2526 // block other optimizations.
2527 if (PHI) {
2528 AssumptionCache *AC =
2529 IFI.GetAssumptionCache ? &IFI.GetAssumptionCache(*Caller) : nullptr;
2530 auto &DL = Caller->getParent()->getDataLayout();
2531 if (Value *V = SimplifyInstruction(PHI, {DL, nullptr, nullptr, AC})) {
2532 PHI->replaceAllUsesWith(V);
2533 PHI->eraseFromParent();
2534 }
2535 }
2536
2537 return InlineResult::success();
2538}
